canonical:
  title: 王大妃薦誠寧大君百齋疏
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 諸佛之願勤於濟沉老婆之心切於薦往歸崇苟至饒益遄加念彼仙靈娵予養女姿容端妙性度寬和謂見榮孝於餘生何圖遽淪於早歲嗚呼已矣雖痛傷其奈何寤寐思之第追修以爲務寔趨三寶所在庸展百日之齋施作區區縱涓埃之微末照詳了了卽水月之分明伏願宿障頓除新機擔發追從福成童子遊遍諸方歸命舍衛丈夫往生淨刹
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 王大妃薦誠寧大君百齋疏
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 諸佛之願。勤於濟沉。老婆之心。切於薦往。歸崇苟至。饒益遄加。念彼仙靈。娵予養女。姿容端妙。性度寬和。謂見榮孝於餘生。何圖遽淪於早歲。嗚呼已矣。雖痛傷其奈何。寤寐思之。第追修以爲務。寔趨三寶所在。庸展百日之齋。施作區區。縱涓埃之微末。照詳了了。卽水月之分明。伏願宿障頓除。新機擔發。追從福成童子。遊遍諸方。歸命舍衛丈夫。往生淨刹。
korean:
  title: 왕대비께서 성녕대군을 천도하는 백일재의 소
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 모든 부처님의 원력(願力)은 빠진 것을 구제하는 데 힘쓰시며 노파(老婆)의 마음은 간 사람을 천도하려는 데 간절합니다. 귀의하여 숭배함이 지극하오니 이익을 더하여 주옵소서. 생각하오니, 저 죽은 이는 일찍이 나의 양딸과 혼인하였으며, 자색과 용모가 단정하고 성품과 도량이 너그러워서 영화스러운 효도를 여생(餘生)에 보려 하였더니, 어찌 젊은 나이에 죽을 줄 알았으리요. 아, 그만이로다. 애통하고 상심한들 어찌하리. 자나 깨나 생각하여 천도하기에 힘쓰나이다. 이에 삼보가 계신 곳을 찾아서 백일의 재를 올립니다. 장만한 것은 보잘 것 없어 물방울이나 티끌처럼 작지마는 살펴 비추시기를 물에 달이 뜨듯이 분명하게 하소서. 엎드려 원하나이다. 묵은 업장(業障)이 다 없어지고 새로운 발심(發心)으로 복성동자(福成童子)가 여러 곳에 두루 다니 듯하고, 부처님께 귀의해서 극락세계에 왕생하여지이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1160_010_0190&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Rite of One Hundred Days for Princess Seongyeong, Presented by the Royal Consort
  author: Byeon Gyeyangn
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The vows of all Buddhas labor to save the drowning;
    The heart of an old woman yearns to guide the departed.
    When reverence and devotion reach their deepest,
    Blessings multiply and swiftly descend.

    I think upon the deceased—once joined to my dear daughter,
    With beauty serene and refined,
    With nature generous and broad of mind.
    We hoped to see filial grace bloom in her remaining years,
    Yet who could know death would come so early?
    Alas, it is done. Though the heart aches and grieves,
    What more can be done?

    Waking and sleeping, we dwell upon this thought,
    And strive with all diligence in rites of deliverance.
    We seek out where the Three Treasures dwell,
    And now present this hundred-day observance.
    Our offerings are humble, mere drops of water, specks of dust—
    Yet look upon them as clearly as the moon reflected in still water.

    Humbly we pray:
    May karmic shadows of ages past be wholly dispelled,
    May new resolve bloom forth.
    May the spirit follow the path of the Blessed Child,
    Wandering freely through all realms,
    And taking refuge in the Buddha,
    Be reborn in the Pure Land of Ultimate Bliss.
  footnotes:
    - This is a Buddhist memorial composition requesting the spiritual elevation and rebirth of Princess Seongyeong in the Pure Land, presented by the Royal Consort Wang.
    - The 'Blessed Child' (福成童子) refers to a celestial being in Buddhist cosmology, used here as an aspirational reference for the deceased's spiritual journey.
    - The 'Three Treasures' (三寶) refers to the Buddha, the Dharma (teachings), and the Sangha (monastic community)—the central objects of Buddhist devotion.
